<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-27T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="1040" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1040">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Mail/57: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-27T19:00:00+03:00">March 27,
                                    1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 28—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1072. Foreign Office states that the 11 sacks of prisoners of war mail
                            mentioned in Embassy’s 678 [<hi rend="italic">687</hi>], February 29, 11
                                p.m.,<note n="74" xml:id="d1040fn1">Not printed.</note> plus 10
                            additional sacks subsequently received from Tehran have been turned over
                            to the Commissariat of Communications and will be forwarded to their
                            destination in the near future. An early reply on the general question
                            of rerouting American prisoner of war mail (reference Department’s 525,
                            March 9, 7 p.m.) in transit through the Soviet Union has been
                            promised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>